v 3
d mlmoderator: Robustness diagnostics and visualization for cross-level interactions in multilevel models
d
d mlmoderator provides a unified workflow for probing, plotting, and
d assessing the robustness of two-way cross-level interaction effects
d in mixed-effects models fitted with Stata's -mixed- command.
d
d Commands:
d   mlmcenter   - grand-mean, group-mean, or within-between centering
d   mlmprobe    - simple slopes at selected moderator values
d   mlmjn       - Johnson-Neyman interval (analytical exact solution)
d   mlmplot     - publication-ready interaction plot with confidence bands
d   mlmsummary  - consolidated moderation report
d   mlmvdecomp  - decompose slope variance into fixed vs random components
d   mlmsens     - ICC-shift robustness and leave-one-cluster-out diagnostics
d
d Requires: Stata 14.1 or later
d
d Author: Subir Hait, Michigan State University
d Support: https://github.com/causalfragility-lab/mlmoderator
d
f mlmcenter.ado
f mlmcenter.sthlp
f mlmprobe.ado
f mlmprobe.sthlp
f mlmjn.ado
f mlmjn.sthlp
f mlmplot.ado
f mlmplot.sthlp
f mlmsummary.ado
f mlmsummary.sthlp
f mlmvdecomp.ado
f mlmvdecomp.sthlp
f mlmsens.ado
f mlmsens.sthlp
f mlmoderator.sthlp
f mlmoderator_demo.do
